<PostLayout title="Confront The Ruin" date="August 22, 2022" category="Blackout Poetry" description="Newspaper blackout poetry by Ryan Kopperud. Hidden words unearthed from the everyday — sing, confront the ruin, demand an end to nothing." type="poetry">

<img src="/images/blackout-confront-the-ruin.webp" alt="Blackout poetry: Confront The Ruin — words revealed from a blacked-out newspaper page" loading="lazy" class="w-full max-w-md mx-auto mb-10 rounded-sm shadow-lg" />

<p>don't bore me<br />
sing<br />
confront the ruin<br />
demand an end to nothing<br />
take on the night<br />
no less still<br />
the absence taking its bravest<br />
that work<br />
is no more</p>

</PostLayout>
